        <p>Five Dollars Reward</p>
        <p> A black boy about nineteen years of age, named <name xml:id=""> 
            <hi rend="allCaps">CHARLES</hi></name>, who was bound to the 
            subscriber, to serve until he was twenty one 
            years of age, runaway about the middle of September 
            last. All persons are forewarned against harboring 
            or employing him, under the penalty of 
            the law. The above reward will be paid for 
            securing him in the Cincinnati jail, or for his 
            delivery to the subscriber, living at 
            <place placeType="origin"> the stone house on the Ohio river, 
                four miles above Cincinnati. </place> </p>
        <p>
            <name xml:id=""><hi rend="allCaps">John C. Dunham</hi></name>
        </p>
